misconceptions.inferred_category_name: No conceptual error detected (correct wrap-around right shift)
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that to right-shift an array by one with wrap-around, you must save the last element, shift elements from the end toward the beginning, then write the saved last element into index 0.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No gap: this matches Java’s actual array indexing and assignment behavior. Shifting from right-to-left avoids overwriting values that are still needed, and saving the last element preserves it for wrap-around.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: None (produces correct output for all N >= 0).
